"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046869","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-31","<p>The information requested is not held.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046869/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:25:28.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046869/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046869/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many work capability assessments have included intervention from mental function champions in the last year.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","211809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046870","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Department outsourced the PIP and ESA assessments to providers and the Mental Health Function Champion (MHFC) role is delivered through them. MHFCs are part of a package of resources available to Health Professionals to help them assess claimants with Mental Health needs.</p><p> </p><p>The Department monitors all elements of the provider’s performance including the quality of assessments, which are assessed through an independent audit, with feedback provided to the provider.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046870/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:32:41.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046870/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046870/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Social Security Benefits: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps her Department takes to assess the effectiveness of mental health champions in (a) personal independence payment and (b) work capability assessments.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","211810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046871","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign Secretary and I, alongside other British Government Ministers, routinely raise our concerns about the persecution of religious minorities, including Christians, where this occurs. He recently asked the Bishop of Truro to conduct an independent review of the persecution of Christians around the world to help inform this important area of our work and ensure it is targeted and effective. The Government works with a large number of NGOs, including Open Doors, to help promote and protect freedom of religion or belief. We use information from a wide range of sources to inform our work.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046871/answer",,,,,"211879 ; 211881 ; 211882 ; 211883 ; 211884 ; 211885 ; 211886 ; 211887 ; 211888 ; 211889 ; 211890 ; 211891 ; 211892 ; 211893 ; 211894 ; 211895 ; 211896 ; 211897 ; 211898 ; 211899 ; 211900 ; 211901 ; 211902 ; 211903 ; 211904 ; 211905 ; 211906 ; 211907 ; 211908 ; 211909 ; 211910 ; 211911 ; 211912 ; 211913 ; 211914 ; 211915 ; 211916 ; 211917 ; 211918 ; 211919 ; 211920 ; 211921 ; 211922 ; 211923 ; 211924 ; 211925 ; 211926 ; 211927 ; 211928","2019-01-31T13:02:19.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046871/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046871/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Palestinians: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Palestinian Authority on its inclusion in the Open Doors 2019 World Watch List of the top 50 countries where Christians face persecution.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","211880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046872","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-02-01","<p>Health Professionals undertaking PIP and ESA assessments have at least 2 years post full registration experience (this refers to either UK registration or equivalent overseas registration for non-UK HCPs) or less than 2 years post full registration experience by prior, written agreement with the Department.</p><p> </p><p>All Health Professionals receive training on how to assess the impact of mental health conditions on claimants. This is followed by on-going professional training and support which continues for the duration of their employment in the role.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Mental Health Function Champions support Health Professionals by providing additional expertise about mental health, cognitive, developmental and learning disabilities and can be referred to at any time during the assessment process.</p><p> </p><p>Health Professionals make every attempt to obtain the best evidence available to assist them in undertaking the assessment. This includes accessing evidence from Community Mental Health Teams, psychologists, psychiatrists and other medical professionals. Health Assessment Providers frequently engage with medical experts, charities and relevant stakeholders to strengthen, review and update training programmes for all their assessment staff.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046872/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T13:27:36.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046872/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046872/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Social Security Benefits: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what guidance is provided to assessors for dealing with claimants' with mental health problems in personal independence payment and work capability assessments.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","211811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046873","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2019-01-31","<p>Based on the self-declaration rates held on our system at the time of this question, none have declared as Sikh. This figure is based entirely on people identifying themselves as a Sikh on the Department’s HR system. The option to declare as Sikh is categorised under Religion.</p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is committed to the creation of a diverse and inclusive working environment to ensure staff do not face any barriers to success, and all staff feel supported at work.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046873/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:07:36.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046873/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046873/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2019-01-23","Department for Exiting the European Union: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046874","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-31","<p>The National Institute for Health Research (NIHR), on behalf of the Department, funded £1,495,363 of programme research on myalgic encephalomyelitis (ME), also known as chronic fatigue syndrome (CFS), over the last three financial years (up to 2017/18). Further information on this research is available through the NIHR Journals Library at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.journalslibrary.nihr.ac.uk/programmes/" target="_blank">https://www.journalslibrary.nihr.ac.uk/programmes/</a></p><p>The NIHR welcomes funding applications for research into any aspect of human health, including ME/CFS; it is not usual practice to ring-fence funds for particular topics or conditions. Applications are subject to peer review and judged in open competition, with awards being made on the basis of the importance of the topic to patients and health and care services, value for money and scientific quality.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046874/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T17:21:07.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046874/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046874/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-23","Chronic Fatigue Syndrome: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent funding has been made available for research into myalgic encephalomyelitis.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","211844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046875","Department for International Trade","false","2019-02-04","<p>There are 24 members of staff in the Department for International Trade (including UK Export Finance (UKEF)) who have self-reported as Sikh (as at 31 December 2018) on departmental systems. The Department records Sikhism as a religion.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046875/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-04T10:29:03.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046875/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046875/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-01-23","Department for International Trade: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046876","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign Secretary and I, alongside other British Government Ministers, routinely raise our concerns about the persecution of religious minorities, including Christians, where this occurs. He recently asked the Bishop of Truro to conduct an independent review of the persecution of Christians around the world to help inform this important area of our work and ensure it is targeted and effective. The Government works with a large number of NGOs, including Open Doors, to help promote and protect freedom of religion or belief. We use information from a wide range of sources to inform our work.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046876/answer",,,,,"211879 ; 211880 ; 211882 ; 211883 ; 211884 ; 211885 ; 211886 ; 211887 ; 211888 ; 211889 ; 211890 ; 211891 ; 211892 ; 211893 ; 211894 ; 211895 ; 211896 ; 211897 ; 211898 ; 211899 ; 211900 ; 211901 ; 211902 ; 211903 ; 211904 ; 211905 ; 211906 ; 211907 ; 211908 ; 211909 ; 211910 ; 211911 ; 211912 ; 211913 ; 211914 ; 211915 ; 211916 ; 211917 ; 211918 ; 211919 ; 211920 ; 211921 ; 211922 ; 211923 ; 211924 ; 211925 ; 211926 ; 211927 ; 211928","2019-01-31T13:02:19.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046876/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046876/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Colombia: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Government of Colombia on that country's inclusion in the Open Doors 2019 World Watch List of the top 50 countries where Christians face persecution.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","211881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046877","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-31","<p>The table below shows data the Department (DfT Central Department, the Driver Vehicle &amp; Licensing Agency, the Driver &amp; Vehicle Services Agency, the Maritime &amp; Coastguard Agency and the Vehicle Certification Agency) holds on the number of staff that have indicated that they are Sikh, and whether this information is recorded as an ethnic or religious group as at 31 December 2018.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Department Total</p></td><td><p>Recorded as Ethnic or Religious group</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>Religion</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The figures represent staff on our payroll and does not include contractors and other non-pay employees.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046877/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T13:46:59.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046877/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046877/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-23","Department for Transport: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046878","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-29","<p>The Department encourages all of its employees to provide details of their personal diversity information. This action is voluntary and information is captured via employee input onto the HR SOP system.</p><p> </p><p>Details on whether someone is a Sikh is captured via input of religious belief information.</p><p> </p><p>As at 31<sup>st</sup> December, 12,211 employees (14.8% of DWP’s workforce), have input information on their religious belief. This includes 166 employees who have recorded their information as Sikh, and 852 employees who chosen the ‘prefer not to say’ option.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046878/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-29T12:15:22.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046878/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046878/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Department for Work and Pensions: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Sikhs are employed in her Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046879","Cabinet Office","false","2019-01-30","<p>At the 31st December 2018, 43 civil servants in my Department were recorded as being Sikhs, as a religious group. The Prime Minister's Office is included in this reply.</p>","Norwich North","Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046879/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T13:07:06.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046879/answer","Biography information for Chloe Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046879/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-01-23","Cabinet Office: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046880","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-30","<p>As of 24 January 2018, eight civil servants in the Department were recorded as being Sikh, as a religious group.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046880/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T14:52:26.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046880/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046880/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-23","Department of Health and Social Care: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046881","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) employs around 12,500 staff, a third of whom are UK-based and two thirds local staff. We only hold data centrally for UK-based staff.</p><p>The number of FCO UK-based staff who are Sikhs is 0.75 per cent. The most recent UK census data estimated that Sikhs are 0.7 per cent of the UK population.</p><p>The diversity characteristic used to report this is religion.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046881/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T13:04:12.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046881/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046881/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046882","Home Office","false","2019-02-01","<p>720 employees have declared themselves as Sikh. Recorded as a religious group.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046882/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T13:44:50.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046882/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046882/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-23","Home Office: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046883","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign Secretary and I, alongside other British Government Ministers, routinely raise our concerns about the persecution of religious minorities, including Christians, where this occurs. He recently asked the Bishop of Truro to conduct an independent review of the persecution of Christians around the world to help inform this important area of our work and ensure it is targeted and effective. The Government works with a large number of NGOs, including Open Doors, to help promote and protect freedom of religion or belief. We use information from a wide range of sources to inform our work.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046883/answer",,,,,"211879 ; 211880 ; 211881 ; 211883 ; 211884 ; 211885 ; 211886 ; 211887 ; 211888 ; 211889 ; 211890 ; 211891 ; 211892 ; 211893 ; 211894 ; 211895 ; 211896 ; 211897 ; 211898 ; 211899 ; 211900 ; 211901 ; 211902 ; 211903 ; 211904 ; 211905 ; 211906 ; 211907 ; 211908 ; 211909 ; 211910 ; 211911 ; 211912 ; 211913 ; 211914 ; 211915 ; 211916 ; 211917 ; 211918 ; 211919 ; 211920 ; 211921 ; 211922 ; 211923 ; 211924 ; 211925 ; 211926 ; 211927 ; 211928","2019-01-31T13:02:19.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046883/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046883/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Bangladesh: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Bangladeshi counterpart on its inclusion in the Open Doors 2019 World Watch List of the top 50 countries where Christians face persecution.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","211882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046884","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-30","<p>As at 31 December 2018, the recorded number of personnel who had declared the Sikh faith under the category 'Religion' or 'Faith' is:</p><p> </p><p>Civilian Personnel 130</p><p> </p><p>Regular/Reserve Military Personnel 270</p><p> </p><ul><li>In line with Departmental guidance the figures have been rounded to the nearest 10.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Civilian data is based on all employees who are active, or on paid or unpaid leave of absence and employed in the MOD Main Top Level Budgets or Defence Equipment and Support as of 31 December 2018.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>UK Regulars comprises full-time personnel including Nursing Services, Full Time Reserve Service personnel, Gurkhas, Mobilised Reservists, Military Provost Guard Service, Locally Employed Personnel, British Army, Non Regular Permanent Staff, Approval Managers, Cadet Force Adult Volunteers, and Sponsored Reserves.</li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Totals exclude Locally Engaged Civilians in overseas locations and Royal Fleet Auxiliary personnel for whom this data is not available.</li></ul><p> </p><p>It is not mandatory for personnel to declare their ethnicity and religion, and figures should therefore not be considered definitive. Sikh is recorded as a religion not an ethnic group.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046884/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T15:39:20.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046884/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046884/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-23","Ministry of Defence: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046885","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-01-30","<p>We welcome the Victims’ Commissioner’s report, ‘Compensation without re-traumatisation’, which was published on 23 January.</p><p>We will be considering carefully the report’s findings and recommendations as part of our ongoing review of the Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme. The terms of reference for the review were published on 18 December 2018, and include consideration of how the Scheme can best reflect the changing nature of violent crime, and effectively support victims in their recovery. We intend to publish proposals later this year.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046885/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T18:18:38.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046885/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046885/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-01-23","Criminal Injuries Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the Victims' Commissioner's review of the criminal injuries compensation scheme.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","211872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046886","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-01-28","<p>As at 31<sup>st</sup> March 2018, there are 236 Sikh staff employed within the MoJ; this is based on staff declaring their religious beliefs on the HR system (SOP), the declaration rate stands at 28.3%. This data will be included in the Workforce Monitoring Report. The tentative due date for publication of the Workforce Report is 31<sup>st</sup> January 2019.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046886/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-28T13:21:45.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046886/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046886/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-01-23","Ministry of Justice: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046887","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-30","<p>Highways England is now responsible for the vast majority of the historic railways estate. This includes legacy bridges, abutments, tunnels, cuttings, viaducts and similar properties associated with closed railway lines, and sales. Network Rail is still responsible for a small proportion of disused railway lines which have been retained due to their close proximity or connection to currently operational railway lines. Network Rail’s records however do not distinguish between disused and operational railway lines, and therefore it is not possible to precisely indicate how much disused network they own.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046887/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T14:48:43.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046887/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046887/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-23","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the disused national rail network remains in the ownership of Network Rail.","true","Biography information for Robert Courts","Witney","Robert Courts","211842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046888","Leader of the House","false","2019-01-31","<p>As set out in the answer from the Minister for Constitution, as of the 31st December 2018, 43 civil servants in the Cabinet Office were recorded as being Sikhs, as a religious group.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046888/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T11:16:31.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046888/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046888/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2019-01-23","Leader of the House of Commons: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how many Sikhs are employed in her Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211860"
