"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046918","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-31","<p>The number of frontline inspectors the Health and Safety Executive has employed in each of the last 10 years are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>HSE (including ONR)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1,463</p></td><td><p>1,495</p></td><td><p>1,450</p></td><td><p>1,432</p></td><td><p>1,367</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>HSE (excluding ONR)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>2017/18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1,051</p></td><td><p>1,038</p></td><td><p>1,037</p></td><td><p>988</p></td><td><p>978</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>HSE inspector numbers are as per the respective Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for Nuclear Regulation (ONR) became an independent statutory public corporation on 1 April 2014 and are excluded from 2013/14 onwards.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046918/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T17:00:01.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046918/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046918/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Health and Safety Executive: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many frontline inspectors the Health and Safety Executive has employed in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","211942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046919","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-01-31","<p>The GMPP is a continually evolving portfolio of the Government’s most complex and high risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016-17), 199 officials in BEIS were working on GMPP projects.</p><p>GMPP data for December 2018 (Q3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised.</p><p>This data refers to public sector employees, defined as those who are directly in the employment of the Civil or Crown Service, local government or Arms’ Length Body at the relevant snapshot date, including seconded members of staff who join the team as Civil, Crown or Public servants.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046919/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T16:07:04.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046919/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046919/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-01-23","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211644"
