"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046921","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-01-31","<p>The GMPP is a continually evolving portfolio of the government’s most complex and high risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016-17), 58.8 officials in DCMS were working on GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>GMPP data for December 2018 (Q3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised. At the end of September 2018 (i.e. the latest submitted data, at end of the Quarter 2 reporting period for 2018-19), 127.5 officials in DCMS were working on GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>This data refers to public sector employees, defined as those who are directly in the employment of the Civil or Crown Service, local government or Arms’ Length Body at the relevant snapshot date, including seconded members of staff who join the team as Civil, Crown or Public servants.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046921/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T12:01:11.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046921/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046921/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-01-23"," 
 Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046922","Department for Education","false","2019-02-01","<p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016/17), 201.3[1] civil servants in the Department for Education (DfE) were working on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP).</p><p>The GMPP data for December 2018 (Quarter 3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised. However, to provide a comparator, at the end of September 2018 (the latest submitted data at the end of the Quarter 2 reporting period 2018/19) 815.6 officials in the DfE were working on projects in the GMPP.</p><p>The GMPP is a continually evolving portfolio of the government’s most complex and high-risk projects. Direct comparisons across years should therefore be treated with caution. As projects join and leave the Portfolio throughout the year, it is likely that a comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] Decimal figures denote part time working hours, as calculated by the Infrastructure and Projects Authority.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046922/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T11:09:50.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046922/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046922/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-01-23","Department for Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046923","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign Secretary and I, alongside other British Government Ministers, routinely raise our concerns about the persecution of religious minorities, including Christians, where this occurs. He recently asked the Bishop of Truro to conduct an independent review of the persecution of Christians around the world to help inform this important area of our work and ensure it is targeted and effective. The Government works with a large number of NGOs, including Open Doors, to help promote and protect freedom of religion or belief. We use information from a wide range of sources to inform our work.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046923/answer",,,,,"211879 ; 211880 ; 211881 ; 211882 ; 211883 ; 211884 ; 211885 ; 211886 ; 211887 ; 211888 ; 211889 ; 211890 ; 211891 ; 211892 ; 211893 ; 211894 ; 211895 ; 211896 ; 211898 ; 211899 ; 211900 ; 211901 ; 211902 ; 211903 ; 211904 ; 211905 ; 211906 ; 211907 ; 211908 ; 211909 ; 211910 ; 211911 ; 211912 ; 211913 ; 211914 ; 211915 ; 211916 ; 211917 ; 211918 ; 211919 ; 211920 ; 211921 ; 211922 ; 211923 ; 211924 ; 211925 ; 211926 ; 211927 ; 211928","2019-01-31T13:02:20.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046923/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046923/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Nepal: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Government of Nepal on its inclusion in the Open Doors 2019 World Watch List of the top 50 countries where Christians face persecution.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","211897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046924","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-01-31","<p>Defra provides quarterly data to The Infrastructure and Projects Authority on its Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP) projects including the full time equivalent (FTE) number of public servants and contractors working on those projects.</p><p>Defra had four projects in the GMPP in 2016. These included TEAM2100, Thames Tideway Tunnel and CAP Delivery, which are no longer part of the GMPP. The only Defra project remaining on the portfolio is UnITy.</p><p>Data for Q3 (December) 2018 is not yet available so we have provided Q2 (September) data instead.</p><p>Based on information available we can confirm the following figures:</p><ul><li>Q2 (September) 2016: 93.9 public sector FTE and 186.2 external contractor FTE working across the four projects making a total of 280.1 FTE.</li><li>Q2 (September) 2018: 5.6 public sector FTE and 61 external contractor FTE working on UnITy making a total of 66.6 FTE.</li></ul><p>These figures do not include public sector staff from outside core project teams.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046924/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:38:12.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046924/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046924/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-01-23","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046925","Treasury","false","2019-02-01","<p>As of 31<sup>st</sup> December 2018, 11 civil servants employed by HM Treasury were recorded as being Sikhs, as a religious group. This was 1% of recorded religion.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046925/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T08:35:31.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046925/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046925/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-23","Treasury: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) a religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046926","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union (DExEU) is responsible for overseeing negotiations to leave the EU and establishing the future relationship between the UK and EU. There are currently no DExEU staff who work in the Government Major Projects Portfolio, as was the case in June 2016, as the projects which comprise the suite of EU Exit projects are not managed under the Government Major Projects Portfolio.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046926/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:06:14.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046926/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046926/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2019-01-23","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046927","Department for International Development","false","2019-01-30","<p>The number of Civil Servants in DFID that were working on Government Major Programmes in June 2016 and December 2018 are as follows;</p><p>June 2016: 6 Full-time and 2 Part-time.</p><p>December 2018: 4 Full-time and 4 Part-time.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046927/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T17:44:14.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046927/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046927/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-01-23","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in her Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046928","Scotland Office","false","2019-01-30","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Scotland does not employ staff directly. All staff that join do so on assignment, loan or secondment from other government bodies, principally the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government, who remain the employers.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046928/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T12:38:05.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046928/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046928/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-01-23","Scotland Office: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046929","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Foreign Secretary and I, alongside other British Government Ministers, routinely raise our concerns about the persecution of religious minorities, including Christians, where this occurs. He recently asked the Bishop of Truro to conduct an independent review of the persecution of Christians around the world to help inform this important area of our work and ensure it is targeted and effective. The Government works with a large number of NGOs, including Open Doors, to help promote and protect freedom of religion or belief. We use information from a wide range of sources to inform our work.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046929/answer",,,,,"211879 ; 211880 ; 211881 ; 211882 ; 211883 ; 211884 ; 211885 ; 211886 ; 211887 ; 211888 ; 211889 ; 211890 ; 211891 ; 211892 ; 211893 ; 211894 ; 211895 ; 211896 ; 211897 ; 211899 ; 211900 ; 211901 ; 211902 ; 211903 ; 211904 ; 211905 ; 211906 ; 211907 ; 211908 ; 211909 ; 211910 ; 211911 ; 211912 ; 211913 ; 211914 ; 211915 ; 211916 ; 211917 ; 211918 ; 211919 ; 211920 ; 211921 ; 211922 ; 211923 ; 211924 ; 211925 ; 211926 ; 211927 ; 211928","2019-01-31T13:02:20.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046929/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046929/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Jordan: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Government of Jordan on its inclusion in the Open Doors 2019 World Watch List of the top 50 countries where Christians face persecution.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","211898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046930","Department for International Trade","false","2019-01-29","<p>No Departmental projects have been included within the Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP) since it was founded on 14 July 2016. As such, no civil servants were working on GMPP projects on the dates referred to.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046930/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-29T14:03:34.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046930/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046930/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-01-23","Department for International Trade: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046931","Department for Transport","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP) is a continually evolving portfolio of the government’s most complex and high risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016-17), 320 Full Time Equivalent (FTE) public sector employees were reported as working on the Department for Transport’s GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>GMPP data for December 2018 (Q3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised. At the end of September 2018 (i.e. the latest submitted data, at end of the Quarter 2 reporting period for 2018-19), 361 Full Time Equivalent (FTE) public sector employees were reported as working on the Department for Transport’s GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>Given the different nature of the projects and programmes within the Department for Transport, some of the FTE figures include public sector employees in the relevant arms-length-body.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046931/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:48:21.307Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046931/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046931/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-01-23","Department for Transport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046932","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-01-31","<p>The Government Major Project’s Portfolio (GMPP) is a continually evolving portfolio of the government’s most complex and high risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of June 2016, 845 full time equivalents Civil Servant Project Delivery Professionals were working on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in the Department for Work and Pensions.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of December 2018, 675 full time equivalents Civil Servant Project Delivery Professionals were working on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in the Department for Work and Pensions.</p><p> </p><p>This data refers to public sector employees, defined as those who are directly in the employment of the Civil or Crown Service, local government or Arms’ Length Body at the relevant snapshot date, including seconded members of staff who join the team as Civil, Crown or Public servants.</p><p> </p><p>The data supplied covers Project Delivery Professionals staff paid for from cost centres associated with the GMPP programmes at the dates specified. Other public sector employees will be involved in the delivery of the programmes in some capacity.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046932/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-31T15:08:10.643Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046932/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046932/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Department for Work and Pensions: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in her Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046933","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-02-01","<p>Please see attached tables showing concerns raised by workers and members of the public and concerns investigated by Inspectors.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046933/answer","PQ 211943 Concerns raised by workers and members of the public and investigated by inspectors.pdf","PQ 211943 Concerns raised by workers and members of the public and investigated by inspectors.pdf","Concerns raised by workers and members of the publ","Concerns raised by workers and members of the publ",,"2019-02-01T11:10:51.727Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046933/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046933/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-01-23","Industrial Health and Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many health and safety concerns were reported by (a) workers and (b) members of the public to the Health and Safety Executive; and how many were investigated by inspectors in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","211943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046934","Wales Office","false","2019-01-30","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Wales is not an employer in its own right. The Ministry of Justice are the employer of staff working in the Office. As at 31 December 2018, fewer than five staff had recorded themselves as Sikh as a religious group. To protect the identification of staff, an exact number cannot therefore be provided.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046934/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T12:44:43.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046934/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046934/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2019-01-23","Wales Office: Sikhs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many Sikhs are employed in his Department; and whether they are recorded as (a) an ethnic or (b) religious group.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","211863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046935","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-30","<p>The Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP) is a continually evolving portfolio of the Government’s most complex and high risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two time points will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p> </p><p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016-17), 561.67 officials in the Department and its arm’s length bodies were working on GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>GMPP data for December 2018 (Q3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised. At the end of September 2018 (i.e. the latest submitted data, at end of the Quarter 2 reporting period for 2018-19), 304 officials in the Department and its arm’s length bodies were working on GMPP projects.</p><p> </p><p>This data refers to public sector employees, defined as those who are directly in the employment of the Civil or Crown Service, local government or arm’s length body at the relevant snapshot date, including seconded members of staff who join the team as Civil, Crown or Public servants.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046935/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T14:51:00.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046935/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046935/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-23","Department of Health and Social Care: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046936","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-01-30","<p>The number of full-time equivalent staff working on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio was 11.8 in June 2016 and 18.1 in December 2018.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046936/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T16:04:05.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046936/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046936/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-01-23","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046937","Treasury","false","2019-02-01","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046937/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T08:38:47.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046937/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046937/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-23","Treasury: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046938","Home Office","false","2019-02-01","<p>The GMPP is a continually evolving portfolio of the government’s most com-plex and high-risk projects. Direct comparisons of the GMPP across years should therefore be treated with caution. Projects join and leave the GMPP throughout the year and it is therefore likely that a simple comparison across two points in time will refer to different sets of projects.</p><p>At the end of June 2016 (i.e. the end of the Quarter 1 reporting period for 2016-17), 411.7 FTE officials in the Home Office were working on GMPP projects.</p><p>GMPP data for December 2018 (Q3 2018/19) has not yet been cleared and finalised. At the end of September 2018 (i.e. the latest submitted data, at end of the Quarter 2 reporting period for 2018-19), 481.1 FTE officials in the Home Office were working on GMPP projects.</p><p>This data refers to public sector employees, defined as those who are direct-ly in the employment of the Civil or Crown Service, local government or Arms’ Length Body at the relevant snapshot date, including seconded mem-bers of staff who join the team as Civil, Crown or Public servants.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046938/answer",,,,,,"2019-02-01T10:48:03.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046938/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046938/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-23","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046939","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-30","<p>The Government Major Projects Portfolio (GMPP) is a continually evolving portfolio of the government's most complex and high-risk projects. In June 2016, the Ministry of Defence was working on 33 projects which are part of the GMPP, and for December 2018 this figure was 35.</p><p>There will have been a number of civil servants working on these projects, either directly or indirectly, at any one time. This information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046939/answer",,,,,,"2019-01-30T15:37:58.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046939/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1046939/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-23","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the corrected Answer of 22 January 2019 to Question 206251, how many civil servants in his Department were working part or full-time on projects in the Government Major Projects Portfolio in (a) June 2016 and (b) December 2018.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","211657"
